        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-09-05 12:48:54.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Yuri,\n\nI have seen AAI version 1.1 within the VM setup have its own DMaaP. I am not AAI expert by any means did you reach out to AAI team to make sure what is being done here is ok?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "d5264c0024e98b2353f64808c6483f47321f3872",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 131,
          "name": "Mandeep Khinda",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "Mandeep.Khinda@gmail.com",
          "username": "mkhinda"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-09-05 13:29:08.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI agree with Munir's comments.  This was done because the VM version of AAI has its own instance of the vanilla ONAP message-router.  I am not sure the implications of consolidating them into the global message-router.  What made you guys make this change?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "3ce5bd0f5e3cd0723f395396634bf30c70ae6e69",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 345,
          "name": "Yury Novitsky",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "yury.novitsky@amdocs.com",
          "username": "yuryn"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2017-09-05 13:51:00.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> I agree with Munir's comments.  This was done because the VM\n > version of AAI has its own instance of the vanilla ONAP\n > message-router.  I am not sure the implications of consolidating\n > them into the global message-router.  What made you guys make this\n > change?\nYes, we got confirmation from AAI team. In ONAP AAI DMaaP is the message-router DMaaP.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "f6e79bfa51eb53bfac9cdd4e6156cbd435ec4912",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 131,
          "name": "Mandeep Khinda",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "Mandeep.Khinda@gmail.com",
          "username": "mkhinda"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-09-05 14:57:37.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2 Verified+1\n\nIn that case this is good to go (I didn't like cloning the message-router into AAI in the first place!!).  In the future, to avoid confusion & unnecessary back and forth, I suggest creating a JIRA entity to track something like this.  In this case it could have been a sub-task under OOM-65, or a bug separate from OOM-65 with a description or some context around the conversation had with the AAI team so the reviewers know what is going on.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
